Lloyd-Smith says these findings establish a good ballpark estimate for the survivability of the virus on these surfaces.
Kuritzkes says that based on prior research, it seems that "flat surfaces and hard surfaces are more friendly to viruses than cloth or rough surfaces."
If you can't get to a sink, hand sanitizer is a good backup plan — just make sure it's at least 60% alcohol.
Given the shortage of hand sanitizers in some stores and reports of price-gouging online, there's lots of interest in DIY hand sanitizer.